Peter Obi, presidential candidate of the Labour Party (LP), and Datti Baba-Ahmed, his running mate, held a campaign rally in Minna, the Niger capital, on Thursday. The LP candidates also visited Umar Farouq Bahago, the Emir of Minna, in his palace. Obi and Datti, alongside their wives, also attended a town hall meeting with women in the state. Below are pictures.                         